gurmukhi: ਚੀਟੀ ਕੈ ੳੁਦਰ ਬਿਖੈ ਹਸਤੀ ਸਮਾੲਿ ਕੈਸੇ ਅਤੁਲ ਪਹਾਰ ਭਾਰ ਭ੍ਰਿੰਗੀਨ ੳੁਠਾਵੲੀ
transliteration: Cheetee Kai Udar Bikhai Hasatee Samaai Kaisay , Atul Pahaar Bhaar Bhringeen Outthaavaee ?
translation: As an elephant cannot be contained in the stomach of an ant, as a small flying insect cannot lift the weight of a mountain,

gurmukhi: ਮਾਛਰ ਕੈ ਡੰਗ ਨ ਮਰਤ ਹੈ ਬਸਿਤ ਨਾਗੁ ਮਕਰੀ ਨ ਚੀਤੈ ਜੀਤੈ ਸਰਿ ਨ ਪੂਜਾਵੲੀ
transliteration: Maachhar Kai Dang N Marat Hai Basit Naagu , Makaree N Cheetai Jeetai Sari N Poojaavaee ?
translation: As a mosquito sting cannot kill the king of snakes, a spider can neither win a tiger nor match with it,

gurmukhi: ਤਮਚਰ ੳੁਡਤ ਨ ਪਹੂਚੈ ਅਾਕਾਸ ਬਾਸ ਮੂਸਾ ਤੳੁ ਨ ਪੈਰਤ ਸਮੁੰਦ੍ਰ ਪਾਰ ਪਾਵੲੀ
transliteration: Tamachar Udat N Pahoochai Aakaas Baasa , Moosaa Tau N Pairat Samoundr Paar Paavaee ?
translation: As an owl cannot fly and reach the sky, nor can a rat swim across the ocean and reach the far side,

gurmukhi: ਤੈਸੇ ਪ੍ਰਿਅ ਪ੍ਰੇਮ ਨੇਮ ਅਗਮ ਅਗਾਧਿ ਬੋਧਿ ਗੁਰਮੁਖਿ ਸਾਗਰ ਜਿੳੁ ਬੂੰਦ ਹੁੲਿ ਸਮਾਵੲੀ ॥੭੫॥
transliteration: Taisay Pria Praym Naym Agam Agaadhi Bodhi , Gurmukhi Saagar Jiu Boond Hui Samaavaee ?75?
translation: So are the ethics of love of our beloved Lord difficult and beyond for us to understand. It is a very serious subject. As a drop of water merges with the water of the ocean, so does a devoted Sikh of the Guru becomes one with his beloved Lord. (75)
